<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Distinguished from the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nitschke &amp; Pyrenomyc.Germ" authorityYear="1870" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diaporthe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species based on DNA sequence data and characterised by conidiomata with single necks erumpent through the host bark.
</paragraph>
