<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Three strains representing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; Q. Yang" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe celticola" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="celticola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diaporthe celticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cluster in a well-supported clade (ML/BI = 100/1), and appear closely related to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. acaciigena" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="acaciigena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">D. acaciigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. M. Tian &amp; Q. Yang" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe celticola" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="celticola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diaporthe celticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished based on ITS, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">cal</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">his3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">tef-1α</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">tub2</emphasis>
loci from 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. acaciigena" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="acaciigena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">D. acaciigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(29/473 in ITS, 68/442 in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">cal</emphasis>
, 53/460 in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">his3</emphasis>
, 79/330 in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">tef-1α</emphasis>
, and 49/415 in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">tub2</emphasis>
). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. celticola" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="celticola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">D. celticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by conidiomata with single necks erumpent through the host bark and can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. acaciigena" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="acaciigena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">D. acaciigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by smaller alpha conidia (6-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4 vs. 10-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-6.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158511X581723" author="Crous, PW" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="108 - 156" refId="B5" refString="Crous, PW, Groenewald, JZ, Shivas, RG, Edwards, J, Seifert, KA, Alfenas, AC, Alfenas, RF, Burgess, TI, Carnegie, AJ, Hardy, GESJ, Hiscock, N, Hueberli, D, Jung, T, Louis-Seize, G, Okada, G, Pereira, OL, Stukely, MJC, Wang, W, White, GP, Young, AJ, McTaggart, AR, Pascoe, IG, Porter, IJ, Quaedvlieg, W, 2011. Fungal Planet description sheets: 69-91. Persoonia 26 (1): 108 - 156, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/003158511X581723" title="Fungal Planet description sheets: 69 - 91." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158511X581723" volume="26" year="2011">Crous et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first occasion that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nitschke &amp; Pyrenomyc.Germ" authorityYear="1870" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diaporthe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have been discovered from infected branches on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cannabaceae" genus="Celtis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Celtis vandervoetiana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vandervoetiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Celtis vandervoetiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and demonstrates it to be a new species based on phylogeny and morphology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
